@prefix ac:    <https://securitybydesign.dev/ontology/appsec-core/v1#> .
@prefix rdf:   <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:  <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix sh:    <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix xsd:   <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# ============================================================
# AppSec Core V1 — Consumer Conformance Shapes (Part B, model invariants)
# ============================================================
#
# ARCHITECTURAL COMMITMENT (programme-lead Pedro Farinha, 2026-05-05 — Option C)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# This file is an ONTOLOGY-OWNED rule artefact. It encodes model invariants
# that AppSec Core V1 imposes on any consumer's normalized claim emission.
# The 5 shapes (M1' / M3 / M4 via CO chain / M4-card cardinality / referential
# integrity) are derived from Decision 0003 + Amendment 1 invariants surfaced
# empirically through Cartographer's substrate work (ESI). Identification
# provenance is historical; OWNERSHIP IS ARCHON.
#
# Lifecycle and discipline:
#
#   1. MAINTAINED BY ARCHON. This file is hand-maintained from the formalised
#      invariants. It is NOT derived from YAML schema and is NOT regenerated
#      by build_shacl.py.
#
#   2. NOT TOUCHED by build_shacl.py. The build script regenerates ONLY
#      appsec-core-v0-shapes.ttl (the 6 schema-derived ontology shapes:
#      Slice / ControlObjective / Practice / Mechanism / Artifact /
#      EvidencePattern). Re-running build_shacl.py must never modify this
#      file. The regression in commit 7ee0373 (which regenerated
#      appsec-core-v0-shapes.ttl from scratch and stripped the consolidated
#      claim shapes) prompted the Option C architectural ratification on
#      2026-05-05.
#
#   3. APPARATUS COMPOSITION. apparatus-shacl-pyshacl-vN tags declare
#      composition explicitly: appsec-core-v0-shapes.ttl @ <commit> +
#      consumer-conformance-shapes.ttl @ <commit>. Pyshacl runners load
#      both files as merged shapes graph before validation. Single SHACL
#      concern (ontology validation) preserved; the split is operational
#      (schema-derived regenerable vs invariant-derived hand-maintained),
#      not semantic.
#
#   4. CROSS-PERSONA UPDATE PROTOCOL. When Decision 0003 receives an
#      amendment that alters model invariants, Cartographer/ESI emits a
#      handover dispatcher to Archon at
#      sbd-ai-runtime/handover/em-curso/YYYY-MM-DD-cartographer-archon-decision-0003-amendment-N-shapes-update.md
#      Archon then updates THIS FILE in a dedicated commit. Apparatus tag
#      refresh follows under programme-lead authority. Archon does NOT
#      monitor ESI for amendments; receives via dispatcher per §0.5.
#
# Provenance:
#
#   Owner:        Archon (sbd-toe-ontology)
#   Authority:    Decision 0003 Amendment 1 (ratified 2026-05-03 by programme-lead
#                 Pedro Farinha) at
#                 ExternalSourcesInventory/agentic/decisions/
#                 0003-normalization-algorithm-redesign-2026-05-03-amendment-1-claims-not-chains.md
#   Architectural ratification: programme-lead Pedro Farinha 2026-05-05 — Option C
#                 (consumer-conformance-shapes.ttl declared ontology-owned)
#   Brief:        ExternalSourcesInventory/agentic/briefs/
#                 2026-05-03-archon-part-b-model-invariant-shacl.md
#   Original:     This file shipped 2026-05-03 in commit f25eb48; consolidated
#                 into appsec-core-v0-shapes.ttl on 2026-05-04 (apparatus-v2
#                 at ee73c19). On 2026-05-05 the consolidation was reversed
#                 (Option C) and this file restored as a separate ontology-
#                 owned artefact.
#   Companion artefact: AppSec Core V1 SBERT embeddings release artefact at
#                 formal/appsec_core/08-embeddings/ (tag
#                 appsec-core-embeddings-v1.0; same canonical IRI scheme; same
#                 consumer contract).
#
# ============================================================
# Purpose
# ============================================================
#
# These shapes enforce the model-side invariants that any consumer of the
# AppSec Core V1 ontology must satisfy when emitting normalized claims
# against the model. They are deliberately consumer-agnostic: the same
# shape graph evaluates Cartographer's PIPELINE 2 substrate (item + claim
# nodes per Amendment 1 §D), a future Manual KG, an MCP plugin's emission,
# and any other downstream artefact alike.
#
# The shapes target the `claim` node (per Amendment 1 §D), not the `item`
# node. The seven-invariant pre-amendment catalogue collapses to:
#
#   M1' Slice coherence on claim   — SHACL (this file). Universal.
#   M2  CO ∈ Slice                 — SHACL (this file). Subsumed by M1' for
#                                    CO-level claims; documented but no
#                                    additional shape; M1' covers it.
#   M3  Practice ∈ CO consistency  — SHACL (this file).
#   M4  Mechanism ∈ Practice       — SHACL (this file). NOTE: V1 OWL skin
#                                    declares `objective_implemented_by_mechanism`
#                                    as CO → Mechanism (NOT Practice → Mechanism);
#                                    M4 is enforced via the CO chain, not via
#                                    the YAML-only `supports_practices`
#                                    relation. See ONTOLOGY GAP 1 below.
#   M4-card Cardinalities V1 asserts — SHACL (this file). Encoded as
#                                    referential-integrity + claim-schema
#                                    cardinalities, since intrinsic ontology
#                                    cardinalities are already enforced on
#                                    ont_graph by the apparatus shapes.
#   M5  Semantic warrant            — process-side, NOT in this file
#                                    (Cartographer Pydantic + threshold check).
#   P1' GROUNDED ⇒ ≥1 claim        — process-side, NOT in this file
#                                    (Cartographer Pydantic + assertion).
#
# ============================================================
# Inventory of V1 ontology relations consumed by these shapes
# ============================================================
#
# All three relations are formally declared in the V1 OWL skin
# (packages/ontology/appsec-core/v1.0/formal/appsec-core-v0-bounded-v1.ttl)
# and have non-empty instance triples in the bounded export:
#
#   ac:belongsToSlice                       owl:ObjectProperty
#                                           rdfs:domain ac:AppSecCoreEntity
#                                           rdfs:range  ac:Slice
#                                           triples: 257
#                                           apparatus cardinality (intrinsic):
#                                             sh:minCount 1 sh:maxCount 1
#                                             on Slice / CO / Practice /
#                                             Mechanism / Artifact /
#                                             EvidencePattern shapes
#
#   ac:objective_realized_by_practice       owl:ObjectProperty
#                                           rdfs:domain ac:ControlObjective
#                                           rdfs:range  ac:Practice
#                                           triples: 125
#                                           apparatus cardinality: sh:minCount 1
#                                             on ControlObjectiveShape
#
#   ac:objective_implemented_by_mechanism   owl:ObjectProperty
#                                           rdfs:domain ac:ControlObjective
#                                           rdfs:range  ac:Mechanism
#                                           triples: 143
#                                           apparatus cardinality: sh:minCount 1
#                                             on ControlObjectiveShape
#
# ============================================================
# Ontology gaps flagged for programme-lead (informational; not blocking)
# ============================================================
#
# GAP 1 — V1 OWL skin declares no formal Practice ↔ Mechanism relation.
#         The components-draft YAML carries `supports_practices` (Mechanism
#         → list of Practices) but that relation is not promoted to the OWL
#         skin. Decision 0003 Amendment 1 §A wording for M4 is "Mechanism ∈
#         Practice", but the ontology actually asserts CO ↔ Mechanism
#         directly. M4 is enforced here via the CO chain (charitable
#         reading); a Mechanism appearing in a slice is valid iff some CO
#         in that slice implements it. If programme-lead intends a stricter
#         M4 (Mechanism's slice via its parent Practice), the V1 OWL skin
#         must formally declare a Practice↔Mechanism relation first.
#
# GAP 2 (inherited from Part A inspection 2026-05-03) — EvidencePattern has
#         zero normalized instances in V1. Claims of `level = "EvidencePattern"`
#         cannot be validated until instances are authored. M5/M3/M4 do not
#         currently apply at this level; this file does not target it.
#
# GAP 3 (inherited from Part A inspection 2026-05-03) — Artifact entities
#         have no description prose (median 2 augmented-words). Artifact is
#         not in the algorithm's claim levels (Amendment 1 §D restricts
#         level ∈ {CO, Practice, Mechanism}); this file does not target it.
#
# Programme-lead decision required only for GAP 1 if a stricter M4 is
# intended; GAPs 2-3 are paper-citable future-work entries.
#
# ============================================================
# Canonical IRI scheme (mirrors Part A augmentation rule v1.0)
# ============================================================
#
#   Slice              ac:SliceASC<NN>          e.g., ac:SliceASC07
#   ControlObjective   ac:ACO_<FAM>_<NNN>       e.g., ac:ACO_IVF_002
#   Practice           ac:ACP_<FAM>_<NNN>       e.g., ac:ACP_IVF_002
#   Mechanism          ac:ACM_<FAM>_<NNN>       e.g., ac:ACM_IVF_002
#
# Consumer claims that join via ont_graph MUST emit `ac:target_core_entity`
# values that are exactly these IRIs. Consumers that emit alternative IRI
# schemes (e.g., `ac:co-ACO-IVF-002` as the v3.2/v4.x substrate did — see
# the SHACL-SLICE-COMPLETENESS-DIAGNOSIS-2026-05-03.md Step 5 finding) WILL
# fail referential integrity here, by construction.
#
# ============================================================
# Consumer claim-node contract (from Decision 0003 Amendment 1 §D)
# ============================================================
#
# Each claim node in a consumer's data graph carries:
#
#   rdf:type                ac:Claim
#   ac:claim_id             xsd:string  (1)
#   ac:target_core_entity   IRI matching the canonical scheme above (1)
#   ac:level                xsd:string  (1; one of "CO" / "Practice" / "Mechanism")
#   ac:slice                IRI of the form ac:SliceASC<NN> (1)
#   ac:similarity_score     xsd:decimal (1; 0.0 .. 1.0)
#   ac:disambiguation_margin xsd:decimal (1; 0.0 .. 1.0)
#   ac:lifted_row_ref       xsd:string  (1)
#   ac:item_ref             IRI of an ac:Item node (1)
#
# These cardinalities are encoded in `ClaimWellFormednessShape` below.
# Any consumer that wants to extend the claim node with additional
# diagnostic properties (e.g., `ac:rationale_snippet`,
# `ac:ablation_baseline_score` per §D) is free to do so without violating
# this shape file; sh:closed is NOT used here, so additive extensions are
# admitted.
#
# ============================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Shape: ClaimWellFormednessShape (claim-schema cardinalities)
# Catches malformed claim emissions before deeper join shapes evaluate.
# Maps to the M4-card family for the claim node specifically (intrinsic
# ontology cardinalities on entities are validated by the apparatus on
# ont_graph; here we validate the claim-node schema the consumer emits).
# ------------------------------------------------------------
ac:ClaimWellFormednessShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ac:Claim ;
    sh:name "Claim well-formedness" ;
    sh:description "Every ac:Claim must carry exactly one target_core_entity, one level in {CO,Practice,Mechanism}, one slice IRI, one similarity_score, one disambiguation_margin, plus a claim_id and item_ref for traceability. Catches malformed claim emissions early." ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path ac:target_core_entity ;
        sh:nodeKind sh:IRI ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:severity sh:Violation ;
        sh:message "M4-card: every ac:Claim must declare exactly one ac:target_core_entity (IRI of a CO / Practice / Mechanism in the AppSec Core V1 ontology)." ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path ac:level ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:in ( "CO" "Practice" "Mechanism" ) ;
        sh:severity sh:Violation ;
        sh:message "M4-card: ac:Claim ac:level must be exactly one of \"CO\" / \"Practice\" / \"Mechanism\" (per Decision 0003 Amendment 1 §D)." ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path ac:slice ;
        sh:nodeKind sh:IRI ;
        sh:class ac:Slice ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:severity sh:Violation ;
        sh:message "M4-card: ac:Claim ac:slice must be exactly one IRI typed as ac:Slice in the ontology graph (ont_graph)." ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path ac:similarity_score ;
        sh:datatype xsd:decimal ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:minInclusive 0.0 ;
        sh:maxInclusive 1.0 ;
        sh:severity sh:Violation ;
        sh:message "M4-card: ac:Claim ac:similarity_score must be exactly one decimal in [0.0, 1.0]." ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path ac:disambiguation_margin ;
        sh:datatype xsd:decimal ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:minInclusive 0.0 ;
        sh:maxInclusive 1.0 ;
        sh:severity sh:Violation ;
        sh:message "M4-card: ac:Claim ac:disambiguation_margin must be exactly one decimal in [0.0, 1.0]." ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path ac:claim_id ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minLength 1 ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:severity sh:Violation ;
        sh:message "M4-card: ac:Claim ac:claim_id must be exactly one non-empty string for traceability." ;
    ] ;

    sh:property [
        sh:path ac:item_ref ;
        sh:nodeKind sh:IRI ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:severity sh:Violation ;
        sh:message "M4-card: ac:Claim ac:item_ref must be exactly one IRI pointing to the parent ac:Item node." ;
    ] .


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Shape: SliceCoherenceClaimShape  (M1' — universal, subsumes M2)
# For every claim, the declared slice MUST equal the ontology's
# belongsToSlice of the target entity. Joins via ont_graph.
#
# This is the single most load-bearing shape: it is the SHACL expression
# of the slice-coherence invariant programme-lead ratified 2026-05-03
# (and the failure-mode whose 769-violation count Cartographer's audit
# enumerated on the v4.2 substrate).
#
# Subsumes M2: when claim.level = "CO", the target's belongsToSlice IS
# the CO's slice membership; the join match enforces CO ∈ Slice
# automatically. Documented; no separate M2 shape.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
ac:SliceCoherenceClaimShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ac:Claim ;
    sh:name "Slice coherence on claim (M1')" ;
    sh:description "Every claim's declared slice must equal the slice the AppSec Core V1 ontology asserts via ac:belongsToSlice for the claim's target entity. Universal across claim levels (CO / Practice / Mechanism). Subsumes M2 (CO ∈ Slice) for CO-level claims. Requires ont_graph non-null at validation time; the validator script enforces this." ;
    sh:sparql [
        sh:message "M1' violation: claim ac:slice does not equal the ontology's ac:belongsToSlice for the claim's target. The substrate has emitted a claim whose target lives in a different slice than the one declared. (Either the slice classifier or the target picker is wrong; not a SHACL-fixable data issue. See Decision 0003 Amendment 1 §A.M1'.)" ;
        sh:prefixes ac: ;
        sh:select """
            PREFIX ac: <https://securitybydesign.dev/ontology/appsec-core/v1#>
            SELECT $this ?declared_slice ?actual_slice ?target
            WHERE {
                $this ac:slice ?declared_slice .
                $this ac:target_core_entity ?target .
                ?target ac:belongsToSlice ?actual_slice .
                FILTER (?declared_slice != ?actual_slice)
            }
        """ ;
    ] .


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Shape: PracticeCOConsistencyShape  (M3)
# For Practice-level claims, the target Practice must be
# objective_realized_by_practice of at least one CO whose belongsToSlice
# equals claim.slice. This catches Practices declared in slice X that no
# CO in slice X realizes — a Practice can satisfy M1' (its own
# belongsToSlice matches the claim) and still violate M3 if no CO in that
# slice picks it up (orphan-practice failure mode).
# ------------------------------------------------------------
ac:PracticeCOConsistencyShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ac:Claim ;
    sh:name "Practice-in-CO consistency (M3)" ;
    sh:description "For every claim where ac:level = \"Practice\", the target Practice must be objective_realized_by_practice of at least one CO whose ac:belongsToSlice equals the claim's ac:slice. Enforces that the Practice is reachable from the slice via the ontology's CO→Practice relation. Requires ont_graph non-null." ;
    sh:sparql [
        sh:message "M3 violation: a Practice-level claim names a Practice that no CO in the declared slice realizes (no CO in claim.slice has ac:objective_realized_by_practice pointing at this Practice). The Practice may be slice-coherent on its own (M1') but is structurally orphan from the slice's CO set." ;
        sh:prefixes ac: ;
        sh:select """
            PREFIX ac: <https://securitybydesign.dev/ontology/appsec-core/v1#>
            SELECT $this ?practice ?slice
            WHERE {
                $this ac:level "Practice" .
                $this ac:slice ?slice .
                $this ac:target_core_entity ?practice .
                FILTER NOT EXISTS {
                    ?co ac:objective_realized_by_practice ?practice .
                    ?co ac:belongsToSlice ?slice .
                }
            }
        """ ;
    ] .


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Shape: MechanismCOConsistencyShape  (M4 — charitable reading via CO chain)
# For Mechanism-level claims, the target Mechanism must be
# objective_implemented_by_mechanism of at least one CO whose
# belongsToSlice equals claim.slice.
#
# IMPORTANT: per ontology gap 1 (top of file), V1 OWL declares
# objective_implemented_by_mechanism as CO → Mechanism direct, not via
# Practice. The brief's "Mechanism ∈ Practice" wording is implemented
# here via the CO chain. If programme-lead later requires the strict
# Mechanism ↔ Practice constraint, this shape needs revision after the
# ontology is extended.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
ac:MechanismCOConsistencyShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ac:Claim ;
    sh:name "Mechanism-in-CO consistency (M4 via CO chain)" ;
    sh:description "For every claim where ac:level = \"Mechanism\", the target Mechanism must be objective_implemented_by_mechanism of at least one CO whose ac:belongsToSlice equals the claim's ac:slice. Enforces that the Mechanism is reachable from the slice via the ontology's CO→Mechanism relation. NOTE: V1 OWL skin asserts CO → Mechanism directly (not via Practice); see ontology gap 1. Requires ont_graph non-null." ;
    sh:sparql [
        sh:message "M4 violation: a Mechanism-level claim names a Mechanism that no CO in the declared slice implements (no CO in claim.slice has ac:objective_implemented_by_mechanism pointing at this Mechanism). The Mechanism may be slice-coherent on its own (M1') but is structurally orphan from the slice's CO set." ;
        sh:prefixes ac: ;
        sh:select """
            PREFIX ac: <https://securitybydesign.dev/ontology/appsec-core/v1#>
            SELECT $this ?mechanism ?slice
            WHERE {
                $this ac:level "Mechanism" .
                $this ac:slice ?slice .
                $this ac:target_core_entity ?mechanism .
                FILTER NOT EXISTS {
                    ?co ac:objective_implemented_by_mechanism ?mechanism .
                    ?co ac:belongsToSlice ?slice .
                }
            }
        """ ;
    ] .


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Shape: ClaimTargetReferentialIntegrityShape (M4-card — referential)
# For every claim, the target IRI must resolve to an entity in the
# ontology graph that is typed appropriately for the claim's level.
# Catches typos and IRI-scheme drift (e.g., the v3.2/v4.x substrate's
# ac:co-ACO-IVF-002 vs the canonical ac:ACO_IVF_002 — that mismatch
# was the deepest failure layer diagnosed in
# SHACL-SLICE-COMPLETENESS-DIAGNOSIS-2026-05-03.md Step 5).
# ------------------------------------------------------------
ac:ClaimTargetReferentialIntegrityShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ac:Claim ;
    sh:name "Claim target referential integrity (M4-card)" ;
    sh:description "For every claim, the target_core_entity IRI must resolve to a node in the ontology graph (ont_graph) whose rdf:type matches the claim's ac:level (CO ↔ ac:ControlObjective, Practice ↔ ac:Practice, Mechanism ↔ ac:Mechanism). Catches IRI typos, IRI-scheme drift, and consumer emission of targets the V1 ontology does not declare." ;
    sh:sparql [
        sh:message "M4-card / referential integrity violation: the claim's ac:target_core_entity IRI does not resolve to an ontology entity whose rdf:type matches the claim's ac:level. Either the IRI is unknown (typo or IRI-scheme drift — e.g., emitting ac:co-ACO-IVF-002 instead of the canonical ac:ACO_IVF_002) or the entity exists at a different ontology level than the claim declares." ;
        sh:prefixes ac: ;
        sh:select """
            PREFIX ac:   <https://securitybydesign.dev/ontology/appsec-core/v1#>
            PREFIX rdf:  <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
            SELECT $this ?target ?level ?expected_type
            WHERE {
                $this ac:target_core_entity ?target .
                $this ac:level ?level .
                BIND ( IF ( ?level = "CO",        ac:ControlObjective,
                       IF ( ?level = "Practice",  ac:Practice,
                       IF ( ?level = "Mechanism", ac:Mechanism,
                            ac:UnknownLevel ))) AS ?expected_type )
                FILTER NOT EXISTS {
                    ?target rdf:type ?expected_type .
                }
            }
        """ ;
    ] .


# ============================================================
# End of consumer-conformance-shapes.ttl
# ============================================================
#
# Per-invariant coverage matrix:
#
#   M1' Slice coherence on claim     SliceCoherenceClaimShape
#   M2  CO ∈ Slice                   subsumed by M1' for level=CO
#   M3  Practice ∈ CO consistency    PracticeCOConsistencyShape
#   M4  Mechanism ∈ CO chain         MechanismCOConsistencyShape (via CO; gap 1)
#   M4-card  Cardinalities           ClaimWellFormednessShape +
#                                    ClaimTargetReferentialIntegrityShape
#
# Out of scope (process-side, Cartographer enforces by construction):
#   M5  Semantic warrant (similarity_score ≥ E2 ∧ disambiguation_margin ≥ E3)
#   P1' GROUNDED ⇒ |claims[]| ≥ 1
#
# Validator: scripts/consumer_conformance_validator.py (parametric;
# loads ont_graph non-null; runs pyshacl with all three graphs).
